{% comment %}
  Order-confirmation page for ONE order, addressed by its ecommerce order
  number: `/checkout/thank-you?order=16220039`. That is the only param the
  page carries.

  Nothing monetary is passed in the URL. The `aicoCheckoutThankYouPage`
  Alpine component fetches the PERSISTED totals from
  /checkout/order-summary, so the amounts shown are always what the aico
  order actually charged — not client-supplied numbers a shopper could
  edit in the address bar.

  The order save runs asynchronously (queued SaveAicoShopOrder), so the
  card has three states:
    - `pending`  — the order exists but is still saving. The component
                   subscribes to the AicoShopOrderCreatedEvent broadcast
                   for this order and swaps in the totals the moment it
                   lands (polling only when pusher is unavailable).
    - `summary`  — confirmed: the persisted breakdown, discount included.
    - `notFound` — no such order, or one outside this shopper's
                   organisation. Enforced server-side by the endpoint.
  A reload, or a link opened later by a colleague on the same debtor,
  lands straight in the `summary` state.

  The legacy `?order_number=…&subtotal=…` / `?orderRef=…` forms still
  render: Adyen's returnUrl is built from a single app-wide
  ADYEN_BASE_REDIRECT_URL that the legacy b2b-shop thank-you page also
  consumes, so it keeps the old dialect (orderRef + sessionId/sessionResult).
  The component verifies the payment session via /checkout/payment-status
  before showing the success card, then rewrites the URL to `?order=`.

  Status medallion: the success card SERVER-RENDERS the processing state
  (sweeping spinner arc + "is being processed" heading + aria-busy), exactly
  like the preorder confirmation — landing here straight after submit must
  never flash a green checkmark over an order that is still saving. Alpine
  flips `is-confirmed` on the card once the totals are in and CSS runs the
  hand-off from there: the orange spinner fades out while a green ring draws
  itself closed on the SAME circumference, the disc pops in behind it, the
  checkmark strokes on top and the confirmed copy rises in underneath. Every
  step is a CSS transition on one class flip — no JS timers — and the whole
  sequence collapses to its final frame under prefers-reduced-motion.

  Background color: the page gutters take the current selected brand's
  `color_schema.checkoutConfirmation.bg` (exposed on
  `customer.aico_selected_brand.aico_checkout_confirmation_bg_color`), applied at
  render time as `--aico-confirmation-bg` so there is no flash. Same treatment as
  the preorder confirmation; the centered white card stays readable on any brand
  color and falls back to the default page background when the brand sets none.
{% endcomment %}

{%- assign aico_confirmation_bg = customer.aico_selected_brand.aico_checkout_confirmation_bg_color -%}

{%- comment -%} `order` is the canonical param; `order_number` / `orderRef` are
  the legacy dialects kept for old bookmarks and the Adyen return leg. {%- endcomment -%}
{%- assign ty_order_number = request.query.order | default: request.query.order_number | default: request.query.orderRef -%}

{% capture ty_success_card %}
    <div class="aico-checkout-thank-you-card"
         :class="{ 'is-confirmed': !pending && !notFound, 'is-not-found': notFound }"
         :aria-busy="pending && !notFound ? 'true' : 'false'">

      {%- comment -%} Spinner and checkmark are the SAME medallion: all four
        circles share one geometry (r=24 on a 52×52 box, C ≈ 151), so the
        sweeping arc and the drawn success ring sit on exactly the same
        circumference and the swap reads as one continuous shape rather than
        two icons replacing each other.

        The warning disc + triangle are the third state on that same geometry
        and the reason the medallion is no longer x-show'd away on notFound:
        landing here without a resolvable order used to leave the card headed
        by nothing at all. It now says so with an icon. {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="aico-ty-status" aria-hidden="true" :class="{ 'aico-ty-status--warn': notFound }">
        <svg class="aico-ty-status-svg" viewBox="0 0 52 52" focusable="false" role="presentation">
          <circle class="aico-ty-status-track" cx="26" cy="26" r="24"/>
          <circle class="aico-ty-status-spin" cx="26" cy="26" r="24"/>
          <circle class="aico-ty-status-ring" cx="26" cy="26" r="24"/>
          <circle class="aico-ty-status-disc" cx="26" cy="26" r="24"/>
          <path class="aico-ty-status-check" d="M14.1 27.2l7.1 7.2 16.7-16.8"/>
          <circle class="aico-ty-status-warn-disc" cx="26" cy="26" r="24"/>
          <path class="aico-ty-status-warn-triangle" d="M26 15.4 38.4 36.6 13.6 36.6 Z"/>
          <path class="aico-ty-status-warn-bang" d="M26 22.6V29.4"/>
          <circle class="aico-ty-status-warn-dot" cx="26" cy="33.1" r="1.45"/>
        </svg>
      </div>

      {%- comment -%} The processing heading is the server-rendered default; the
        confirmed one is x-cloak'd so it can never paint before Alpine knows the
        order is saved. aria-live announces the swap to screen readers.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <h1 class="aico-checkout-thank-you-title" aria-live="polite">
        <span x-show="pending && !notFound">{{ 'checkout.thank_you.processing_title' | t }}</span>
        <span class="aico-ty-reveal" x-show="!pending && !notFound" x-cloak>{{ 'checkout.thank_you.title' | t }}</span>
        {%- comment -%} Two distinct dead ends under one medallion: the page was
          opened with no order reference at all (a bare `/checkout/thank-you`,
          typically a locale switch or a hand-edited URL), or with one that does
          not resolve. Same icon, different heading — telling the shopper "not
          found" about an order they never named is just confusing.
        {%- endcomment -%}
        <span x-show="notFound && !orderNumber && !orderId" x-cloak>{{ 'checkout.thank_you.missing_reference_title' | t }}</span>
        <span x-show="notFound && (orderNumber || orderId)" x-cloak>{{ 'checkout.thank_you.not_found_title' | t }}</span>
      </h1>

      <p class="aico-checkout-thank-you-order" x-show="orderNumber && !notFound">
        {{ 'checkout.thank_you.order_number' | t }}:
        <strong x-text="orderNumber">{{ ty_order_number }}</strong>
      </p>

      {%- comment -%} Still saving: the totals are not trustworthy yet, so show
        the wait state rather than a half-filled or query-supplied breakdown.
        Server-rendered (no x-cloak) — it belongs to the processing state the
        page lands in. {%- endcomment -%}
      <p class="aico-checkout-thank-you-confirming" x-show="pending && !notFound">
        {{ 'checkout.thank_you.confirming' | t }}
      </p>

      {%- comment -%} Authoritative totals read back from the persisted aico
        order (aico_shop_orders + the ecommerce order's discount line item) —
        exactly what the backend charged, including the promo-code discount. {%- endcomment -%}
      <dl class="aico-checkout-thank-you-totals aico-ty-reveal" x-show="summary" x-cloak>
        <div class="aico-checkout-summary-row">
          <dt>{{ 'checkout.summary.subtotal' | t }}</dt>
          <dd x-text="formatSummary('subtotal')"></dd>
        </div>
        <div class="aico-checkout-summary-row aico-checkout-summary-row-discount"
             x-show="summaryValue('discount_value') > 0">
          <dt>
            {{ 'checkout.summary.discount' | t }}<template x-if="summary && summary.discount_code"><span> (<span x-text="summary.discount_code"></span>)</span></template>
          </dt>
          <dd x-text="'−' + formatSummary('discount_value')"></dd>
        </div>
        <div class="aico-checkout-summary-row" x-show="summaryValue('shipping') > 0">
          <dt>{{ 'checkout.summary.shipping' | t }}</dt>
          <dd x-text="formatSummary('shipping')"></dd>
        </div>
        <div class="aico-checkout-summary-row" x-show="summaryValue('vat') > 0">
          <dt>{{ 'checkout.summary.vat' | t }}</dt>
          <dd x-text="formatSummary('vat')"></dd>
        </div>
        <div class="aico-checkout-summary-row" x-show="summaryValue('cc_fee') > 0">
          <dt>{{ 'checkout.summary.cc_fee' | t }}</dt>
          <dd x-text="formatSummary('cc_fee')"></dd>
        </div>
        <div class="aico-checkout-summary-row aico-checkout-summary-row-grand">
          <dt>{{ 'checkout.summary.total' | t }}</dt>
          <dd x-text="formatSummary('total')"></dd>
        </div>
      </dl>

      {%- comment -%} The confirmation mail only goes out once the order is
        actually saved, so this claim waits for the confirmed state too. {%- endcomment -%}
      <p class="aico-checkout-thank-you-email aico-ty-reveal" x-show="!pending && !notFound" x-cloak>{{ 'checkout.thank_you.email_confirmation' | t }}</p>

      {%- comment -%} Unknown order number, or one belonging to another
        organisation — /checkout/order-summary answers 404 either way and never
        says which, so the page cannot be used to probe for orders. {%- endcomment -%}
      <p class="aico-checkout-thank-you-not-found" x-show="notFound && (orderNumber || orderId)" x-cloak>
        {{ 'checkout.thank_you.not_found' | t }}
      </p>
      <p class="aico-checkout-thank-you-not-found" x-show="notFound && !orderNumber && !orderId" x-cloak>
        {{ 'checkout.thank_you.missing_reference' | t }}
      </p>

      {%- comment -%} A dead end needs a way out of itself: the shopper's own
        orders, not just the catalogue. {%- endcomment -%}
      <p class="aico-checkout-thank-you-not-found-links" x-show="notFound" x-cloak>
        <a href="{{ routes.aico_account_orders_url }}" class="aico-button aico-button-primary">
          {{ 'checkout.thank_you.view_orders' | t }}
        </a>
      </p>

      <a href="{{ routes.products_url }}" class="aico-button aico-button-primary" x-show="!notFound">
        {{ 'checkout.thank_you.continue' | t }}
      </a>
      <a href="{{ routes.products_url }}" class="aico-button aico-button-outline" x-show="notFound" x-cloak>
        {{ 'checkout.thank_you.continue' | t }}
      </a>
    </div>
{% endcapture %}

<main class="aico-checkout-thank-you"{% if aico_confirmation_bg %} style="--aico-confirmation-bg: {{ aico_confirmation_bg | escape }};"{% endif %}>
  <div class="aico-page-container">
    {%- comment -%} The component is mounted for EVERY confirmation (not just the
      Adyen return leg): it also fetches the persisted order totals via
      /checkout/order-summary. Without session params init() resolves the state
      to 'success' immediately. {%- endcomment -%}
      <div x-data="aicoCheckoutThankYouPage" x-init="init()">
        <template x-if="state === 'verifying'">
          <div class="aico-checkout-thank-you-card">
            <div class="aico-checkout-processing-spinner" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="40" height="40" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
                <path d="M21 12a9 9 0 1 1-6.219-8.56"/>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <p class="aico-checkout-thank-you-email">{{ 'checkout.thank_you.verifying' | t }}</p>
          </div>
        </template>

        <template x-if="state === 'success'">
          {{ ty_success_card }}
        </template>

        <template x-if="state === 'cancelled'">
          <div class="aico-checkout-thank-you-card aico-checkout-payment-error">
            <h1 class="aico-checkout-thank-you-title">{{ 'checkout.payment_error.title' | t }}</h1>
            <p>{{ 'checkout.payment_error.cancelled' | t }}</p>
            {% if ty_order_number %}
              <p>
                {{ 'checkout.payment_error.reference_number' | t }}
                <strong>{{ ty_order_number }}</strong>{{ 'checkout.payment_error.customer_service' | t }}
              </p>
            {% endif %}
            <p>{{ 'checkout.payment_error.order_not_placed' | t }}</p>
            <p>{{ 'checkout.payment_error.no_reservation' | t }}</p>
            <p>
              {{ 'checkout.payment_error.questions_before_email' | t }}
              <a href="mailto:partner@kybunjoya.swiss"><strong>partner@kybunjoya.swiss</strong></a>{{ 'checkout.payment_error.questions_after_email' | t }}
            </p>
            <p>{{ 'checkout.payment_error.thank_you' | t }}</p>
          </div>
        </template>

        <template x-if="state === 'unverified'">
          <div class="aico-checkout-thank-you-card aico-checkout-payment-error">
            <h1 class="aico-checkout-thank-you-title">{{ 'checkout.payment_error.unverified_title' | t }}</h1>
            <p>{{ 'checkout.payment_error.unverified' | t }}</p>
            {% if ty_order_number %}
              <p>
                {{ 'checkout.payment_error.reference_number' | t }}
                <strong>{{ ty_order_number }}</strong>{{ 'checkout.payment_error.customer_service' | t }}
              </p>
            {% endif %}
            <p>
              {{ 'checkout.payment_error.questions_before_email' | t }}
              <a href="mailto:partner@kybunjoya.swiss"><strong>partner@kybunjoya.swiss</strong></a>{{ 'checkout.payment_error.questions_after_email' | t }}
            </p>
          </div>
        </template>
      </div>
  </div>
</main>
